# Copy to ".env" or ".env.production" and adjust, or leave unset to use built-in defaults.
#
# Any non-empty value overrides automatic resolution in src/api/api.js:
#   - npm run dev       → defaults to http://localhost:3000/api
#   - npm run build     → defaults to /api (same domain as the deployed frontend)
#
# Examples (pick one style for your deployment):
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000/api
# VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com/api
# VITE_API_URL=/api
#
# Docker: place `.env` or `.env.production` next to the Dockerfile before `docker build`
# (they are copied into the image build stage; see Dockerfile), or pass:
#   docker build --build-arg VITE_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com/api .
